            "title": "Mark Zuckerberg arrives to testify in social media addiction trial",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>STORY: :: Mark Zuckerberg arrives at court for his first day of questioning on youth social media addiction</p><p>\n              :: Los Angeles, California / February 18, 2026</p><!-- Article --><p>\n              While Zuckerberg has previously testified on the subject before Congress, the stakes are higher at the jury trial in Los Angeles, California. Meta may have to pay damages if it loses the case, and the verdict could erode Big Tech's longstanding legal defense against claims of user harm.</p><p>\n              The lawsuit and others like it are part of a global backlash against social media platforms over children's mental health.</p><p>\n              The case involves a California woman who started using Meta's Instagram and Google's YouTube as a child. She alleges the companies sought to profit by hooking kids on their services despite knowing social media could harm their mental health. She alleges the apps fueled her depression and suicidal thoughts and is seeking to hold the companies liable.</p><p>\n              Meta and Google have denied the allegations, and pointed to their work to add features that keep users safe. Meta has often pointed to a National Academies of Sciences finding that research does not show social media changes kids' mental health.</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/mark-zuckerberg-arrives-to-testify-in-social-media-addiction-trial-ce7e5ddfd981f124",
            "pub_date": "2026-02-19 03:29:34",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
